{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"This is a picture of Maurice Druon,"},{"time":3000,"text":"the Honorary Perpetual Secretary of L'Academie francaise,"},{"time":7000,"text":"the French Academy."},{"time":9000,"text":"He is splendidly attired in his 68,000-dollar uniform,"},{"time":14000,"text":"befitting the role of the French Academy"},{"time":17000,"text":"as legislating the"},{"time":20000,"text":"correct usage in French"},{"time":22000,"text":"and perpetuating the language."},{"time":24000,"text":"The French Academy has two main tasks:"},{"time":27000,"text":"it compiles a dictionary of official French."},{"time":30000,"text":"They're now working on their ninth edition,"},{"time":33000,"text":"which they began in 1930, and they've reached the letter P."},{"time":37000,"text":"They also legislate on correct usage,"},{"time":40000,"text":"such as the proper term for what the French call \"email,\""},{"time":44000,"text":"which ought to be \"courriel.\""},{"time":46000,"text":"The World Wide Web, the French are told,"},{"time":48000,"text":"ought to be referred to as"},{"time":50000,"text":"\"la toile d'araignee mondiale\" -- the Global Spider Web --"},{"time":54000,"text":"recommendations that the French gaily ignore."}]},{"cues":[{"time":59000,"text":"Now, this is one model of how language comes to be:"},{"time":63000,"text":"namely, it's legislated by an academy."},{"time":66000,"text":"But anyone who looks at language realizes"},{"time":69000,"text":"that this is a rather silly conceit,"},{"time":73000,"text":"that language, rather, emerges from human minds interacting from one another."},{"time":76000,"text":"And this is visible in the unstoppable change in language --"},{"time":80000,"text":"the fact that by the time the Academy finishes their dictionary,"},{"time":83000,"text":"it will already be well out of date."}]},{"cues":[{"time":85000,"text":"We see it in the"},{"time":87000,"text":"constant appearance of slang and jargon,"},{"time":91000,"text":"of the historical change in languages,"},{"time":93000,"text":"in divergence of dialects"},{"time":95000,"text":"and the formation of new languages."},{"time":98000,"text":"So language is not so much a creator or shaper of human nature,"},{"time":101000,"text":"so much as a window onto human nature."},{"time":104000,"text":"In a book that I'm currently working on,"},{"time":107000,"text":"I hope to use language to shed light on"},{"time":110000,"text":"a number of aspects of human nature,"},{"time":112000,"text":"including the cognitive machinery"},{"time":114000,"text":"with which humans conceptualize the world"},{"time":117000,"text":"and the relationship types that govern human interaction."},{"time":120000,"text":"And I'm going to say a few words about each one this morning."}]},{"cues":[{"time":123000,"text":"Let me start off with a technical problem in language"},{"time":125000,"text":"that I've worried about for quite some time --"},{"time":127000,"text":"and indulge me"},{"time":131000,"text":"in my passion for verbs and how they're used."},{"time":134000,"text":"The problem is, which verbs go in which constructions?"},{"time":137000,"text":"The verb is the chassis of the sentence."},{"time":140000,"text":"It's the framework onto which the other parts are bolted."}]},{"cues":[{"time":144000,"text":"Let me give you a quick reminder"},{"time":146000,"text":"of something that you've long forgotten."},{"time":148000,"text":"An intransitive verb, such as \"dine,\" for example,"},{"time":151000,"text":"can't take a direct object."},{"time":153000,"text":"You have to say, \"Sam dined,\" not, \"Sam dined the pizza.\""},{"time":156000,"text":"A transitive verb mandates"},{"time":158000,"text":"that there has to be an object there:"},{"time":160000,"text":"\"Sam devoured the pizza.\" You can't just say, \"Sam devoured.\""},{"time":163000,"text":"There are dozens or scores of verbs of this type,"},{"time":167000,"text":"each of which shapes its sentence."},{"time":169000,"text":"So, a problem in explaining how children learn language,"},{"time":173000,"text":"a problem in teaching language to adults so that they don't make grammatical errors,"},{"time":178000,"text":"and a problem in programming computers to use language is"},{"time":181000,"text":"which verbs go in which constructions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":184000,"text":"For example, the dative construction in English."},{"time":186000,"text":"You can say, \"Give a muffin to a mouse,\" the prepositional dative."},{"time":189000,"text":"Or, \"Give a mouse a muffin,\" the double-object dative."},{"time":192000,"text":"\"Promise anything to her,\" \"Promise her anything,\" and so on."},{"time":196000,"text":"Hundreds of verbs can go both ways."},{"time":198000,"text":"So a tempting generalization for a child,"},{"time":200000,"text":"for an adult, for a computer"},{"time":202000,"text":"is that any verb that can appear in the construction,"},{"time":204000,"text":"\"subject-verb-thing-to-a-recipient\""},{"time":207000,"text":"can also be expressed as \"subject-verb-recipient-thing.\""},{"time":210000,"text":"A handy thing to have,"},{"time":212000,"text":"because language is infinite,"},{"time":214000,"text":"and you can't just parrot back the sentences that you've heard."},{"time":217000,"text":"You've got to extract generalizations"},{"time":219000,"text":"so you can produce and understand new sentences."},{"time":222000,"text":"This would be an example of how to do that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":224000,"text":"Unfortunately, there appear to be idiosyncratic exceptions."},{"time":227000,"text":"You can say, \"Biff drove the car to Chicago,\""},{"time":230000,"text":"but not, \"Biff drove Chicago the car.\""},{"time":233000,"text":"You can say, \"Sal gave Jason a headache,\""},{"time":236000,"text":"but it's a bit odd to say, \"Sal gave a headache to Jason.\""},{"time":239000,"text":"The solution is that these constructions, despite initial appearance,"},{"time":242000,"text":"are not synonymous,"},{"time":244000,"text":"that when you crank up the microscope"},{"time":246000,"text":"on human cognition, you see that there's a subtle difference"},{"time":248000,"text":"in meaning between them."},{"time":250000,"text":"So, \"give the X to the Y,\""},{"time":252000,"text":"that construction corresponds to the thought"},{"time":255000,"text":"\"cause X to go to Y.\" Whereas \"give the Y the X\""},{"time":258000,"text":"corresponds to the thought \"cause Y to have X.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":262000,"text":"Now, many events can be subject to either construal,"},{"time":266000,"text":"kind of like the classic figure-ground reversal illusions,"},{"time":269000,"text":"in which you can either pay attention"},{"time":272000,"text":"to the particular object,"},{"time":274000,"text":"in which case the space around it recedes from attention,"},{"time":278000,"text":"or you can see the faces in the empty space,"},{"time":280000,"text":"in which case the object recedes out of consciousness."},{"time":284000,"text":"How are these construals reflected in language?"},{"time":286000,"text":"Well, in both cases, the thing that is construed as being affected"},{"time":290000,"text":"is expressed as the direct object,"},{"time":292000,"text":"the noun after the verb."},{"time":294000,"text":"So, when you think of the event as causing the muffin to go somewhere --"},{"time":298000,"text":"where you're doing something to the muffin --"},{"time":300000,"text":"you say, \"Give the muffin to the mouse.\""},{"time":302000,"text":"When you construe it as \"cause the mouse to have something,\""},{"time":305000,"text":"you're doing something to the mouse,"},{"time":307000,"text":"and therefore you express it as, \"Give the mouse the muffin.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":310000,"text":"So which verbs go in which construction --"},{"time":312000,"text":"the problem with which I began --"},{"time":314000,"text":"depends on whether the verb specifies a kind of motion"},{"time":318000,"text":"or a kind of possession change."},{"time":320000,"text":"To give something involves both causing something to go"},{"time":323000,"text":"and causing someone to have."},{"time":325000,"text":"To drive the car only causes something to go,"},{"time":328000,"text":"because Chicago's not the kind of thing that can possess something."},{"time":330000,"text":"Only humans can possess things."},{"time":333000,"text":"And to give someone a headache causes them to have the headache,"},{"time":335000,"text":"but it's not as if you're taking the headache out of your head"},{"time":338000,"text":"and causing it to go to the other person,"},{"time":340000,"text":"and implanting it in them."},{"time":342000,"text":"You may just be loud or obnoxious,"},{"time":344000,"text":"or some other way causing them to have the headache."},{"time":346000,"text":"So, that's"},{"time":350000,"text":"an example of the kind of thing that I do in my day job."}]},{"cues":[{"time":352000,"text":"So why should anyone care?"},{"time":354000,"text":"Well, there are a number of interesting conclusions, I think,"},{"time":357000,"text":"from this and many similar kinds of analyses"},{"time":361000,"text":"of hundreds of English verbs."},{"time":363000,"text":"First, there's a level of fine-grained conceptual structure,"},{"time":366000,"text":"which we automatically and unconsciously compute"},{"time":369000,"text":"every time we produce or utter a sentence, that governs our use of language."},{"time":373000,"text":"You can think of this as the language of thought, or \"mentalese.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":377000,"text":"It seems to be based on a fixed set of concepts,"},{"time":380000,"text":"which govern dozens of constructions and thousands of verbs --"},{"time":383000,"text":"not only in English, but in all other languages --"},{"time":386000,"text":"fundamental concepts such as space,"},{"time":388000,"text":"time, causation and human intention,"},{"time":391000,"text":"such as, what is the means and what is the ends?"},{"time":394000,"text":"These are reminiscent of the kinds of categories"},{"time":396000,"text":"that Immanuel Kant argued"},{"time":398000,"text":"are the basic framework for human thought,"},{"time":401000,"text":"and it's interesting that our unconscious use of language"},{"time":404000,"text":"seems to reflect these Kantian categories."},{"time":407000,"text":"Doesn't care about perceptual qualities,"},{"time":409000,"text":"such as color, texture, weight and speed,"},{"time":411000,"text":"which virtually never differentiate"},{"time":413000,"text":"the use of verbs in different constructions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":416000,"text":"An additional twist is that all of the constructions in English"},{"time":419000,"text":"are used not only literally,"},{"time":421000,"text":"but in a quasi-metaphorical way."},{"time":424000,"text":"For example, this construction, the dative,"},{"time":426000,"text":"is used not only to transfer things,"},{"time":428000,"text":"but also for the metaphorical transfer of ideas,"},{"time":431000,"text":"as when we say, \"She told a story to me\""},{"time":433000,"text":"or \"told me a story,\""},{"time":435000,"text":"\"Max taught Spanish to the students\" or \"taught the students Spanish.\""},{"time":438000,"text":"It's exactly the same construction,"},{"time":440000,"text":"but no muffins, no mice, nothing moving at all."},{"time":444000,"text":"It evokes the container metaphor of communication,"},{"time":447000,"text":"in which we conceive of ideas as objects,"},{"time":449000,"text":"sentences as containers,"},{"time":451000,"text":"and communication as a kind of sending."},{"time":453000,"text":"As when we say we \"gather\" our ideas, to \"put\" them \"into\" words,"},{"time":456000,"text":"and if our words aren't \"empty\" or \"hollow,\""},{"time":458000,"text":"we might get these ideas \"across\" to a listener,"},{"time":461000,"text":"who can \"unpack\" our words to \"extract\" their \"content.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":464000,"text":"And indeed, this kind of verbiage is not the exception, but the rule."},{"time":467000,"text":"It's very hard to find any example of abstract language"},{"time":470000,"text":"that is not based on some concrete metaphor."},{"time":473000,"text":"For example, you can use the verb \"go\""},{"time":476000,"text":"and the prepositions \"to\" and \"from\""},{"time":478000,"text":"in a literal, spatial sense."},{"time":480000,"text":"\"The messenger went from Paris to Istanbul.\""},{"time":482000,"text":"You can also say, \"Biff went from sick to well.\""},{"time":485000,"text":"He needn't go anywhere. He could have been in bed the whole time,"},{"time":488000,"text":"but it's as if his health is a point in state space"},{"time":490000,"text":"that you conceptualize as moving."},{"time":492000,"text":"Or, \"The meeting went from three to four,\""},{"time":494000,"text":"in which we conceive of time as stretched along a line."},{"time":497000,"text":"Likewise, we use \"force\" to indicate"},{"time":500000,"text":"not only physical force,"},{"time":502000,"text":"as in, \"Rose forced the door to open,\""},{"time":504000,"text":"but also interpersonal force,"},{"time":506000,"text":"as in, \"Rose forced Sadie to go,\" not necessarily by manhandling her,"},{"time":510000,"text":"but by issuing a threat."},{"time":512000,"text":"Or, \"Rose forced herself to go,\""},{"time":514000,"text":"as if there were two entities inside Rose's head,"},{"time":517000,"text":"engaged in a tug of a war."}]},{"cues":[{"time":519000,"text":"Second conclusion is that the ability to conceive"},{"time":522000,"text":"of a given event in two different ways,"},{"time":525000,"text":"such as \"cause something to go to someone\""},{"time":527000,"text":"and \"causing someone to have something,\""},{"time":529000,"text":"I think is a fundamental feature of human thought,"},{"time":533000,"text":"and it's the basis for much human argumentation,"},{"time":536000,"text":"in which people don't differ so much on the facts"},{"time":539000,"text":"as on how they ought to be construed."},{"time":541000,"text":"Just to give you a few examples:"},{"time":543000,"text":"\"ending a pregnancy\" versus \"killing a fetus;\""},{"time":545000,"text":"\"a ball of cells\" versus \"an unborn child;\""},{"time":548000,"text":"\"invading Iraq\" versus \"liberating Iraq;\""},{"time":550000,"text":"\"redistributing wealth\" versus \"confiscating earnings.\""},{"time":554000,"text":"And I think the biggest picture of all"},{"time":556000,"text":"would take seriously the fact"},{"time":559000,"text":"that so much of our verbiage about abstract events"},{"time":562000,"text":"is based on a concrete metaphor"},{"time":564000,"text":"and see human intelligence itself"},{"time":566000,"text":"as consisting of a repertoire of concepts --"},{"time":569000,"text":"such as objects, space, time, causation and intention --"},{"time":572000,"text":"which are useful in a social, knowledge-intensive species,"},{"time":576000,"text":"whose evolution you can well imagine,"},{"time":578000,"text":"and a process of metaphorical abstraction"},{"time":581000,"text":"that allows us to bleach these concepts"},{"time":583000,"text":"of their original conceptual content --"},{"time":586000,"text":"space, time and force --"},{"time":589000,"text":"and apply them to new abstract domains,"},{"time":591000,"text":"therefore allowing a species that evolved"},{"time":594000,"text":"to deal with rocks and tools and animals,"},{"time":596000,"text":"to conceptualize mathematics, physics, law"},{"time":599000,"text":"and other abstract domains."}]},{"cues":[{"time":602000,"text":"Well, I said I'd talk about two windows on human nature --"},{"time":605000,"text":"the cognitive machinery with which we conceptualize the world,"},{"time":608000,"text":"and now I'm going to say a few words about the relationship types"},{"time":610000,"text":"that govern human social interaction,"},{"time":612000,"text":"again, as reflected in language."},{"time":615000,"text":"And I'll start out with a puzzle, the puzzle of indirect speech acts."},{"time":619000,"text":"Now, I'm sure most of you have seen the movie \"Fargo.\""},{"time":621000,"text":"And you might remember the scene in which"},{"time":623000,"text":"the kidnapper is pulled over by a police officer,"},{"time":626000,"text":"is asked to show his driver's license"},{"time":628000,"text":"and holds his wallet out"},{"time":630000,"text":"with a 50-dollar bill extending"},{"time":633000,"text":"at a slight angle out of the wallet."},{"time":635000,"text":"And he says, \"I was just thinking"},{"time":637000,"text":"that maybe we could take care of it here in Fargo,\""},{"time":639000,"text":"which everyone, including the audience,"},{"time":642000,"text":"interprets as a veiled bribe."},{"time":645000,"text":"This kind of indirect speech is rampant in language."},{"time":649000,"text":"For example, in polite requests,"},{"time":651000,"text":"if someone says, \"If you could pass the guacamole,"},{"time":653000,"text":"that would be awesome,\""},{"time":655000,"text":"we know exactly what he means,"},{"time":657000,"text":"even though that's a rather bizarre"},{"time":659000,"text":"concept being expressed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":661000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":664000,"text":"\"Would you like to come up and see my etchings?\""},{"time":666000,"text":"I think most people"},{"time":668000,"text":"understand the intent behind that."},{"time":671000,"text":"And likewise, if someone says,"},{"time":673000,"text":"\"Nice store you've got there. It would be a real shame if something happened to it\" --"},{"time":676000,"text":"(Laughter) --"},{"time":677000,"text":"we understand that as a veiled threat,"},{"time":679000,"text":"rather than a musing of hypothetical possibilities."},{"time":682000,"text":"So the puzzle is, why are bribes,"},{"time":685000,"text":"polite requests, solicitations and threats so often veiled?"},{"time":688000,"text":"No one's fooled."},{"time":690000,"text":"Both parties know exactly what the speaker means,"},{"time":693000,"text":"and the speaker knows the listener knows"},{"time":695000,"text":"that the speaker knows that the listener knows, etc., etc."},{"time":698000,"text":"So what's going on?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":700000,"text":"I think the key idea is that language"},{"time":702000,"text":"is a way of negotiating relationships,"},{"time":704000,"text":"and human relationships fall into a number of types."},{"time":707000,"text":"There's an influential taxonomy by the anthropologist Alan Fiske,"},{"time":711000,"text":"in which relationships can be categorized, more or less,"},{"time":714000,"text":"into communality, which works on the principle"},{"time":716000,"text":"\"what's mine is thine, what's thine is mine,\""},{"time":719000,"text":"the kind of mindset that operates within a family, for example;"},{"time":723000,"text":"dominance, whose principle is \"don't mess with me;\""},{"time":726000,"text":"reciprocity, \"you scratch my back, I'll scratch yours;\""},{"time":730000,"text":"and sexuality, in the immortal words of Cole Porter, \"Let's do it.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":735000,"text":"Now, relationship types can be negotiated."},{"time":738000,"text":"Even though there are default situations"},{"time":741000,"text":"in which one of these mindsets can be applied,"},{"time":743000,"text":"they can be stretched and extended."},{"time":746000,"text":"For example, communality applies most naturally"},{"time":749000,"text":"within family or friends,"},{"time":751000,"text":"but it can be used to try to transfer"},{"time":753000,"text":"the mentality of sharing"},{"time":755000,"text":"to groups that ordinarily would not be disposed to exercise it."},{"time":759000,"text":"For example, in brotherhoods, fraternal organizations,"},{"time":763000,"text":"sororities, locutions like \"the family of man,\""},{"time":766000,"text":"you try to get people who are not related"},{"time":768000,"text":"to use the relationship type that would ordinarily"},{"time":772000,"text":"be appropriate to close kin."}]},{"cues":[{"time":774000,"text":"Now, mismatches -- when one person assumes one relationship type,"},{"time":777000,"text":"and another assumes a different one -- can be awkward."},{"time":780000,"text":"If you went over and you helped yourself"},{"time":782000,"text":"to a shrimp off your boss' plate,"},{"time":784000,"text":"for example, that would be an awkward situation."},{"time":786000,"text":"Or if a dinner guest after the meal"},{"time":788000,"text":"pulled out his wallet and offered to pay you for the meal,"},{"time":791000,"text":"that would be rather awkward as well."},{"time":793000,"text":"In less blatant cases,"},{"time":796000,"text":"there's still a kind of negotiation that often goes on."},{"time":799000,"text":"In the workplace, for example,"},{"time":801000,"text":"there's often a tension over whether an employee"},{"time":803000,"text":"can socialize with the boss,"},{"time":805000,"text":"or refer to him or her"},{"time":807000,"text":"on a first-name basis."},{"time":809000,"text":"If two friends have a"},{"time":811000,"text":"reciprocal transaction, like selling a car,"},{"time":813000,"text":"it's well known that this can be a source"},{"time":815000,"text":"of tension or awkwardness."},{"time":817000,"text":"In dating, the transition"},{"time":819000,"text":"from friendship to sex"},{"time":821000,"text":"can lead to, notoriously, various forms of awkwardness,"},{"time":824000,"text":"and as can sex in the workplace,"},{"time":826000,"text":"in which we call the conflict between a"},{"time":828000,"text":"dominant and a sexual relationship \"sexual harassment.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":832000,"text":"Well, what does this have to do with language?"},{"time":834000,"text":"Well, language, as a social interaction,"},{"time":836000,"text":"has to satisfy two conditions."},{"time":838000,"text":"You have to convey the actual content --"},{"time":841000,"text":"here we get back to the container metaphor."},{"time":843000,"text":"You want to express the bribe, the command, the promise,"},{"time":846000,"text":"the solicitation and so on,"},{"time":848000,"text":"but you also have to negotiate"},{"time":850000,"text":"and maintain the kind of relationship"},{"time":852000,"text":"you have with the other person."},{"time":854000,"text":"The solution, I think, is that we use language at two levels:"},{"time":857000,"text":"the literal form signals"},{"time":859000,"text":"the safest relationship with the listener,"},{"time":861000,"text":"whereas the implicated content --"},{"time":864000,"text":"the reading between the lines that we count on the listener to perform --"},{"time":867000,"text":"allows the listener to derive the interpretation"},{"time":869000,"text":"which is most relevant in context,"},{"time":871000,"text":"which possibly initiates a changed relationship."}]},{"cues":[{"time":874000,"text":"The simplest example of this is in the polite request."},{"time":878000,"text":"If you express your request as a conditional --"},{"time":881000,"text":"\"if you could open the window, that would be great\" --"},{"time":884000,"text":"even though the content is an imperative,"},{"time":886000,"text":"the fact that you're not using the imperative voice"},{"time":889000,"text":"means that you're not acting as if you're in a relationship of dominance,"},{"time":893000,"text":"where you could presuppose the compliance of the other person."},{"time":896000,"text":"On the other hand, you want the damn guacamole."},{"time":898000,"text":"By expressing it as an if-then statement,"},{"time":901000,"text":"you can get the message across"},{"time":903000,"text":"without appearing to boss another person around."}]},{"cues":[{"time":907000,"text":"And in a more subtle way, I think, this works"},{"time":909000,"text":"for all of the veiled speech acts"},{"time":911000,"text":"involving plausible deniability:"},{"time":913000,"text":"the bribes, threats, propositions,"},{"time":915000,"text":"solicitations and so on."},{"time":917000,"text":"One way of thinking about it is to imagine what it would be like"},{"time":919000,"text":"if language -- where it could only be used literally."},{"time":922000,"text":"And you can think of it in terms of a"},{"time":924000,"text":"game-theoretic payoff matrix."},{"time":927000,"text":"Put yourself in the position of the"},{"time":929000,"text":"kidnapper wanting to bribe the officer."},{"time":932000,"text":"There's a high stakes"},{"time":934000,"text":"in the two possibilities"},{"time":937000,"text":"of having a dishonest officer or an honest officer."},{"time":940000,"text":"If you don't bribe the officer,"},{"time":943000,"text":"then you will get a traffic ticket --"},{"time":945000,"text":"or, as is the case of \"Fargo,\" worse --"},{"time":947000,"text":"whether the honest officer"},{"time":949000,"text":"is honest or dishonest."},{"time":951000,"text":"Nothing ventured, nothing gained."},{"time":953000,"text":"In that case, the consequences are rather severe."},{"time":956000,"text":"On the other hand, if you extend the bribe,"},{"time":958000,"text":"if the officer is dishonest,"},{"time":960000,"text":"you get a huge payoff of going free."},{"time":963000,"text":"If the officer is honest, you get a huge penalty"},{"time":966000,"text":"of being arrested for bribery."},{"time":968000,"text":"So this is a rather fraught situation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":970000,"text":"On the other hand, with indirect language,"},{"time":972000,"text":"if you issue a veiled bribe,"},{"time":974000,"text":"then the dishonest officer"},{"time":976000,"text":"could interpret it as a bribe,"},{"time":978000,"text":"in which case you get the payoff of going free."},{"time":981000,"text":"The honest officer can't hold you to it as being a bribe,"},{"time":984000,"text":"and therefore, you get the nuisance of the traffic ticket."},{"time":987000,"text":"So you get the best of both worlds."},{"time":990000,"text":"And a similar analysis, I think,"},{"time":992000,"text":"can apply to the potential awkwardness"},{"time":994000,"text":"of a sexual solicitation,"},{"time":996000,"text":"and other cases where plausible deniability is an asset."},{"time":999000,"text":"I think this affirms"},{"time":1001000,"text":"something that's long been known by diplomats --"},{"time":1003000,"text":"namely, that the vagueness of language,"},{"time":1005000,"text":"far from being a bug or an imperfection,"},{"time":1008000,"text":"actually might be a feature of language,"},{"time":1011000,"text":"one that we use to our advantage in social interactions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1014000,"text":"So to sum up: language is a collective human creation,"},{"time":1017000,"text":"reflecting human nature,"},{"time":1019000,"text":"how we conceptualize reality,"},{"time":1021000,"text":"how we relate to one another."},{"time":1023000,"text":"And then by analyzing the various quirks and complexities of language,"},{"time":1027000,"text":"I think we can get a window onto what makes us tick."},{"time":1030000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1031000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}